---
import ContentPage from '../layouts/ContentPage.astro';

const title = 'Privacy Policy — JSONLab';
const description =
  'JSONLab privacy policy. JSONLab is privacy-first: your JSON is processed entirely in your browser and is never uploaded to our servers.';
const keywords = 'jsonlab privacy policy, json viewer privacy, client-side json tools';
---

<ContentPage title={title} description={description} heading="Privacy Policy" keywords={keywords}>
  <p class="updated">Last updated: June 21, 2026</p>

  <p>
    This Privacy Policy explains how <strong>JSONLab</strong> ("we", "us" or
    "our") handles information when you use our website and tools (the
    "Service"). JSONLab is built to be privacy-first, and this policy reflects
    that commitment.
  </p>

  <h2>1. Your data stays in your browser</h2>
  <p>
    JSONLab is a client-side application. All JSON you paste, type, open or
    convert is processed entirely within your browser on your own device.
    <strong>We do not upload, transmit, store or have any access to the content
    you work with.</strong> Sensitive data such as API payloads, configuration
    files and logs never leaves your machine.
  </p>

  <h2>2. Information we do not collect</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>We do not collect or store the JSON or other content you process.</li>
    <li>We do not require an account, sign-up, or any personal information to use the Service.</li>
    <li>We do not sell or share any personal information, because we do not collect it.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>3. Local storage</h2>
  <p>
    To improve your experience, JSONLab may store small preferences (such as
    your selected theme) in your browser's local storage. This information
    remains on your device, is not transmitted to us, and can be cleared at any
    time through your browser settings.
  </p>

  <h2>4. Cookies and tracking</h2>
  <p>
    JSONLab does not use advertising cookies or third-party tracking scripts.
    The Service is ad-free and does not load third-party analytics or
    tag-manager scripts.
  </p>

  <h2>5. Hosting and server logs</h2>
  <p>
    The website's static files are delivered by a hosting provider. Like most
    web hosts, the provider may automatically record standard technical request
    information (such as IP address, browser type and timestamp) for security
    and operational purposes. This is limited to delivering the page itself and
    does not include the content you process within the app.
  </p>

  <h2>6. Third-party links</h2>
  <p>
    Our Service may contain links to third-party websites. We are not
    responsible for the privacy practices of those sites and encourage you to
    review their privacy policies.
  </p>

  <h2>7. Children's privacy</h2>
  <p>
    The Service is not directed to children under the age of 13, and we do not
    knowingly collect personal information from children.
  </p>

  <h2>8. Changes to this policy</h2>
  <p>
    We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be
    posted on this page with an updated revision date.
  </p>

  <h2>9. Contact us</h2>
  <p>
    If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please reach out
    through our <a href="/contact">Contact</a> page.
  </p>
</ContentPage>
